ce:section.ce:para:
Design-Expert software (version 10.0.3, Stat–Ease Inc., Minneapolis, USA) was employed for CCD, mathematical modelling and optimization of the surface composition of AuNP/CQD−IL/SPCE. Three independent variables considered in the study were the percentage of IL (low 2% and high 4%), amount of CQD (low 8 μg and high 12 μg) and deposition time of AuNP (low 200 s and high 400 s) (Table 1
                        ), whereas the amperometric response of the AuNP/CQD−IL/SPCE towards BPA was the dependent factor. In the design, 20 experiments were conducted with 8 factorial points, 6 axial points and 6 central points and the value of the experimental response was the mean of three replicates. Table 1 shows the high and low levels of each variable. The high and low levels of each variable were selected based on our preliminary studies. CQD and IL were mixed and different amounts of this mixture was pipetted on SPCEs and then AuNP was electrodeposited on the CQD−IL/SPCE to prepare the 20 modified electrodes. Amperometric response currents of the modified electrodes, obtained at +0.60 V in 0.05 M pH 6.5 PBS containing 5.7 × 10−6 M BPA, were used as the response to analyze the experimental design. The design matrix and amperometric currents as the response are presented in Table 2
                        .
